## Penguin Analysis

To analyse the relationship between the bill length and bill depth of the penguins that live in three different islands, I made a scatterplot that plots two of the variables with color verification of three types of species.

```{r}

library(tidyverse)

# Source functions
source(file="C:/Users/shior/OneDrive/Desktop/productive-r-workflow/R/functions.R")

# Read the clean dataset
data <- readRDS(file = "R/01_load_clean_data.R")

# plot function
create_scatterplot <- function(data, selected_species, selected_island) {
  # Filter the data for the specified species and island
  filtered_data <- data %>%
    na.omit() %>%
    filter(species == selected_species, island == selected_island)
  
  # Create the scatterplot
  plot <- ggplot(
    filtered_data,
    aes(x = bill_length_mm, y = bill_depth_mm, color = species, shape = species)
  ) +
    geom_point() +
    labs(
      x = "Bill Length (mm)",
      y = "Bill Depth (mm)",
      title = paste("Penguin Bill Dimensions -", selected_species, "-", selected_island)
    )
  
  return(plot)
}

# Use the function
create_scatterplot(data, "Adelie", "Torgersen")
```

